column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

Gunnedah numbers reduced by half to 1750 good quality cattle with yearlings in the majority. Trends increased significantly with all regular buyers participating.

Light steers to background were substantially dearer  272c to 300c/kg. Steers  280 kgs 292 to 400c/kg with some drafts showing a lapse in quality. Medium steers to feed saw a slight negative correction 359c to 382c/kg whereas similar steers to background sold to a dearer trend 359c to 390c/kg. Heavy yearling feeders gained 5c/kg  and sold 345c to 375c/kg. Light feeder heifers 310c to 337c/kg and medium feeders resulted in a dearer trend 345c to 375c/kg. Heavy feeders also dearer 316c to 330c/kg.

Heavy grown steers were dearer 336c to 356c/kg with the heifers following suite gaining 8c/kg and selling up to 326c/kg. Medium cows were dearer 254c to 260c/kg and heavy cows selling to dearer trends 242c to 305c/kg. Heavy bulls made to 285c/kg.

Stephen Adams MLA
